My footsteps, and the creaking of the hallway...[p]
They sound like screams as their reverberations rock my eardrums.[p]
I had been walking carefully step by step, but without realizing it I had began to run.[p]
There is no sign of anyone.[p]
The silent innards of the school building are dark, and with only the flashlight on my chest it is [p]
impossible for me to see any of the details.[p]
Cheryl doesn't have a flashlight, so if she came in here and got lost, then she probably wouldn't even be able to walk around.[p]
Since I have my flashlight turned on, she should be able to notice me easily...[p]
At least I have that modest hope.[p]
I then notice that I have come to the entrance to the music room.[p]
I place my hand on the heavy door.[p]


[playse  storage="DOOR_OPEN.ogg"  ]
