I gently open the cover over the piano keys.[p]
I notice that there is red mixed in among the black and white.[p]
I try touching the liquid.[p]
It has a lukewarm feel, it is still holding heat.[p]
It is definitely blood.[p]
My heart pounds in my chest like an alarm bell.[p]
The large amount of blood spilled on the keys...[p]
If this is Cheryl's blood, then she may no longer be alive.[p]
I wipe the stain off my hands onto my jeans, stand, and leave the music room.[p]


